Document: NavigationRegion2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationregion2d.rst
Summary: Defines a 2D navigation region for pathfinding.

NavigationRegion2D

Inherits: Node2D < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A 2D navigation region for pathfinding.

This node defines a navigation region that can be used by NavigationServer2D to calculate paths. It is a subclass of Node2D, so it can be transformed in the 2D space.

The navigation region is defined by a NavigationMesh resource. This resource contains the walkable areas and obstacles for pathfinding.

Properties:
enabled (bool): If true, the navigation region is active and will be used by NavigationServer2D. Default: true
get_navigation_mesh() → NavigationMesh: Returns the NavigationMesh resource assigned to this region.
set_navigation_mesh(nav_mesh: NavigationMesh) → void: Sets the NavigationMesh resource for this region.

Methods:
get_navigation_polygon() → NavigationPolygon: Returns the NavigationPolygon resource assigned to this region.
set_navigation_polygon(nav_polygon: NavigationPolygon) → void: Sets the NavigationPolygon resource for this region.

Note: The NavigationRegion2D node is used to define walkable areas in a 2D scene for AI agents. It works in conjunction with the NavigationServer2D to provide pathfinding capabilities. The NavigationMesh resource is crucial for defining the geometry of these walkable areas.
