Document: NavigationRegion2D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationregion2d.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the NavigationRegion2D node, which defines a navigation area in 2D space.

Property: enabled (bool)
Description: Determines if the NavigationRegion2D is enabled or disabled.
Default: true
Setget: set_enabled, is_enabled

Property: enter_cost (float)
Description: When pathfinding enters this region's navigation mesh from another region's navigation mesh, this value is added to the path distance for determining the shortest path.
Default: 0.0
Setget: set_enter_cost, get_enter_cost

Property: navigation_layers (int)
Description: A bitfield determining all navigation layers the region belongs to. These navigation layers can be checked upon when requesting a path with NavigationServer2D.map_get_path.
Default: 1
Setget: set_navigation_layers, get_navigation_layers

Property: navigation_polygon (NavigationPolygon)
Description: The NavigationPolygon resource to use.
Setget: set_navigation_polygon, get_navigation_polygon

Property: travel_cost (float)
Description: When pathfinding moves inside this region's navigation mesh, the traveled distances are multiplied with this value for determining the shortest path.
Default: 1.0
Setget: set_travel_cost, get_travel_cost

Property: use_edge_connections (bool)
Description: If enabled, the navigation region will use edge connections to connect with other navigation regions within proximity of the navigation map edge connection margin.
Default: true
Setget: set_use_edge_connections, get_use_edge_connections
